      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">17 Dec. [18]91 ¶ Immediate ¶ Memorandum, ¶  ¶ Referring to the Government Botanist's letter of the 28th ultimo, ¶  asking to be allowed to remain in his position in order to finish certain scientific ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">91.12.17</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Thomas Wilson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No.6112, pp. 1373-4, unit 95, VPRS 1187/P, outward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">17 Dec. [18]91</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">Immediate</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">Memorandum,</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Referring to the Government Botanist's letter of the 28th ultimo,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to A. McLean, 28 November 1891.</p>
               </note> asking to be allowed to remain in his position in order to finish certain scientific work on which he is engaged, the Public Service Board have made the following minute:-</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">"Before issuing a certificate in this case the Board would require further evidence than has yet been furnished for the necessity of retaining the officer named and desires to know for how long the retention (if granted) will probably be required to enable Baron Von Mueller to complete the scientific work on which he is at present engaged."</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Government Botanist will be so good as to furnish to me as soon as possible the information requisite to enable me to reply.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">T. R. Wilson</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">The Government Botanist.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to T. Wilson, 17 December 1891 (in this edition as 91-12-17a).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
